flowRoot.flowPara: Visualizing RNA Secondary Structure Base Pair Binding Probabilities using Nested Concave Hulls

text.tspan: J. Sansen and R. Bourqui and P. Thebault and J. Allali and D. Auber

flowRoot.flowPara: AbstractThe challenge 1 of the BIOVIS 2015 design contest consists in designing an intuitive visual depiction of base pairs binding probabilities for secondary structure of ncRNA. Our representation depicts the potential nucleotide pairs binding using nested concave hulls over the computed MFE ncRNA secondary structure. Thus, it allows to identify regions with a high level of uncertainty in the MFE computation but also the structures which seem to match to reality.

2. Data Processing: Select sequences of matching pairs

flowRoot.flowPara: Select MFE-rejected sequence of pairs binding using 2 parameters:
mPairs : minimum numbers of pairs in each sequence
nbLevels : numbers of levels of probability required.
Using nbLevels we define a threshold t which determines the minimum base pair probability value.
t = (maxP-minP)/nbLevels
We loop nbLevels times through the matrix increasing t to pick smaller and smaller sets of sequences with higher and higher base pair probability values.
Additionnally, we can tune the threshold in order to filter out of the selectable sets the ones with negligible matching probabilities.

text.tspan: 3. Design: Using Nested Concave Hulls to reflect the uncertainty of pairs binding

flowRoot.flowPara: Potential base pairs binding are emphasized with the addition of nested concave hulls[2] which put forward the subsequences.
This technique makes possible to order and nest hulls by size of sets. Even sets with low pairing probabilities can be depicted and identified while putting forward the most likely sequences.
The more a sub-sequence is wrapped into hulls, the more its probability is important.
The two hulls of a base pairs sequence are connected with a link.
Using a bezier curve bending algorithm[3] we ease the identification of pairwise elements by reducing clutter and links crossings.

text.tspan: reflect the uncertainty of pair binding

flowRoot.flowPara: Effective and intuitive depiction of a ncRNA secondary structure showing the most important potential base-pairs binding rejected during the
MFE-structure computation.

Our method emphasizes the most probable pair bindings and the influence they may have onto the predicted MFE-structure. The use of nested concave hulls produces a pleasant depiction of the potential base pairs binding which reveals the uncertainty in the predicted MFE-structure and the region of the structure that should remain stable with different base-pairs binding.
Multiple hulls over the same regions indicate a high level of uncertainty and a few or no hulls reflect the strength of the prediction for these regions.
